  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This assessment evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 credibility factors. The intended use scope is prediction of normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) in g/100L at nominal operating conditions (5 L/min, 100 mmHg, 3600 RPM) for pre-market submission support. All seven assessed factors achieve required levels under the MRL-5 threshold; six factors were scoped out as not applicable to the submission boundary. Decision: Accepted.",
